{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,200p' DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Design Pattern Notes for Issue 31882\n\n## Relevant Pattern\n\nThe replacement term `GO:1905349` ciliary transition zone assembly follows the cellular component assembly design pattern in `src/design_patterns/cc_assembly.tsv`:\n\n- process: `GO:1905349` ciliary transition zone assembly\n- assembled component: `GO:0035869` ciliary transition zone\n- logical definition: `GO:0022607` cellular component assembly and `results_in_assembly_of GO:0035869`\n\nThe obsoleted term `GO:1905353` ciliary transition fiber assembly also followed this pattern, using `GO:0097539` ciliary transition fiber as the assembled component. The issue decision treats this term as redundant with the broader ciliary transition zone assembly process, so the obsolete stanza removes its logical definition and uses `replaced_by: GO:1905349`.\n\n## Relationship Decision\n\n`GO:0060271` cilium assembly already has `relationship: has_part GO:1905349 ! ciliary transition zone assembly`. The obsolete `starts_with GO:0097711` edge was removed rather than retargeted to avoid asserting that all cilium assembly necessarily starts with the broader replacement process.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
